# Project stack — this repository

This repo is **Cursor Collections** (Eversis): **Cursor** rules, attachable prompts under **`.cursor/prompts/`** (synced into `website/docs/prompts/` for the docs site), skills in **`.cursor/skills/`**, and [documentation/cursor-collection.md](../../documentation/cursor-collection.md).

| Area | This repository |
| ---- | --------------- |
| **Product** | Cursor-native product engineering framework + published workflow docs |
| **Docs site** | Docusaurus 3 under **`website/`** (`cursor-collections-docs`) |
| **Prompts** | **`.cursor/prompts/public/`** and **`internal/`** (`eversis-*.md`); attach with **`@eversis-*`**; **`sync-prompts`** copies to gitignored `website/docs/prompts/` (also in **`.cursorignore`** to avoid double **`@`** indexing) |
| **Skills** | **`.cursor/skills/eversis-*/`** (topic packages; list/read/validate via **`eversis-collections` MCP**, not a separate **Agent Skills** path) |

## Quality commands (this repo)

Run from **`website/`** (see [website/package.json](../../website/package.json)):

- **Dev server:** `npm start` (Docusaurus)
- **Production build:** `npm run build` — use this as the primary quality gate for doc changes
- **Serve build locally:** `npm run serve`

There is no root `lint` / `test` script; the site is mostly Markdown and React theme.

After changes under **`.cursor/`** (rules, prompts, commands, skills), run link validation before merge:

```bash
node scripts/validate-cursor-markdown-links.mjs --context=source
# or from website/:
npm run validate-cursor-links
```

`prebuild` / `prestart` in `website/` already run **`validate-cursor-links`** — broken markdown links fail **`npm run build`**.

## Conventions

- **Specs / plans:** **`docs/specs/<issue-kebab>/`** — `*.research.md`, `*.plan.md`, `*.spec.md` (see **`docs/specs/README.md`**). **In this framework repo**, `docs/specs/*/`, `docs/context/*/`, and `docs/plans/*` (except **`docs/plans/README.md`**) are **gitignored** — local agent artifacts only. Normative BA Docs requirements live on the docs site at **`website/docs/workflow/business-manager-docs.md`** (playbook + normative rules). Legacy flat plans under **`docs/plans/`** are deprecated — prefer `docs/specs/<issue-kebab>/`.
- **Internal notes:** **`docs/context/*.md`** (subfolders local-only in this repo — see **`docs/context/README.md`**)
- **Git commits:** JIRA-style first line — see **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)** and team practice
- **Template** for other projects: see **“Reference: Eversis stack example”** in [documentation/cursor-collection.md](../../documentation/cursor-collection.md)

## Agent skills policy (framework repo)

| Do not load (product skills) | `eversis-implementing-filters`, `eversis-implementing-backend`, `eversis-implementing-frontend`, `eversis-ba-docs-*` — unless a spec explicitly requires them |
| Load for framework work | `eversis-creating-skills`, `eversis-creating-prompts`, `eversis-writing-repo-documentation` |

Consumer projects must replace this block per [installation](../../website/docs/getting-started/installation.md).

## Status: Fine — handoff (mandatory contract)

Aligned with [workflow overview — Status: Fine](../../website/docs/workflow/overview.md):

1. When **all** planned agent work for the Implement thread is finished, declare **`Fine`** (explicit word / status).
2. **In the same assistant response** as **`Fine`**, produce the **QA comment draft** by following **`.cursor/skills/eversis-fine-handoff/SKILL.md`** exactly (read that file if needed, or load via **`eversis-collections` MCP** `eversis_skills_get` for `eversis-fine-handoff`). Do **not** treat [`website/docs/skills/fine-handoff.md`](../../website/docs/skills/fine-handoff.md) as the procedural source of truth — it is onboarding / narrative only; normative procedure is **`SKILL.md`** + MCP ([documentation/cursor-collection.md](../../documentation/cursor-collection.md) § QA handoff after Fine).
3. Label the draft: **`Draft QA comment — review before posting to Jira`** (per [`eversis-engineering-manager.mdc`](eversis-engineering-manager.mdc)).
4. **Never** post to Jira in that turn; publication only after **explicit** human approval (paste or Atlassian MCP).

Skipping the QA draft when declaring **Fine** is a **workflow breach** — if you cannot comply (context limit, blocked tools), say so and stop **without** declaring **Fine**.

**Consumer repos:** downstream projects should mirror this contract in **their** `eversis-project-stack.mdc` (always-on) or equivalent AGENTS guidance when they vendor this framework via submodule / copy.
